Protocooperation is a relationship in which organisms in an association are mutually benefited.This interaction is similar to mutualism, but unlike mutualism, `the relationship is not obligatory` —both organism can survive independently.

#### Marine `Worm–Bacteria` Relationship:
 `Marine worms secrete mucus` from tiny glands on their backs to feed the bacteria. In return, the `bacteria provide` some degree of `insulation` and `protection` to the worms.
